  "body": "## üéâ Description\r\n\r\nI'm using openzeppelin-solidity inside my contract. `truffle compile` command runs smoothly and I managed to deploy my contract to Rinkeby without any issues.\r\n\r\nBut when I try to run `abigen` command, I got some errors. Details below.\r\n\r\n- [x] üêõ This is a bug report.\r\n- [ ] üìà This is a feature request.\r\n\r\n## üíª Environment\r\n\r\n- Which version of OpenZeppelin are you using? = 1.11.0\r\n- What network are you deploying to? = Ganache & Rinkeby, but it's not related to the problem\r\n- How are you deploying your OpenZeppelin-backed contracts? = Truffle\r\n\r\n## üìù Details\r\n\r\nWhen I ran `abigen --sol=ABCtoken.sol --pkg=main --out=ABCtoken.go` command, I got the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nFailed to build Solidity contract: solc: exit status 1\r\nABCtoken.sol:3:1: Error: Source \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC20/MintableToken.sol\" not found: File not found.\r\nimport \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC20/MintableToken.sol\";\r\n^---------------------------------------------------------------------^\r\n```\r\n\r\n## üî¢ Code To Reproduce\r\n\r\n1) Init a Truffle project.\r\n\r\n2) Create a new contract. Name the file as _ABCtoken.sol_.\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.23;\r\n\r\nimport \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC20/MintableToken.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract ABCtoken is MintableToken {\r\n  string public constant name = \"ABCtoken\";\r\n  string public constant symbol = \"ABC\";\r\n  uint8 public constant decimals = 18;\r\n\r\n  constructor() public {\r\n    // make the deployer rich\r\n    balances[msg.sender] = 1000 * 1 ether;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n3) Run `yarn add openzeppelin-solidity` command.\r\n\r\n4) Run `truffle compile` and make sure you see no errors.\r\n\r\n5) `cd` into contracts folder.\r\n\r\n6) Run `abigen --sol=ABCtoken.sol --pkg=main --out=ABCtoken.go`.\r\n\r\n## üëç Other Information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.12-stable\r\nOS & Version: OSX 10.12.6\r\n\r\nI'm not sure this is go-ethereum abigen problem or openzeppelin-solidity problem. üòï\r\n",
