    "body": "When a solidity file is provided to abigen, it compiles the file using solc compiler.\r\nAccording to solidity doc\r\n\r\n> solc only allows you to include files from certain directories: They have to be in the directory (or subdirectory) of one of the explicitly specified source files or in the directory (or subdirectory) of a remapping target.\r\n\r\nCurrently, there is no way to provide remapping target to abigen command. (Issue for the same is raised in geth repo [#16518](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/16518))\r\n\r\nSo all imported files have to be in same directory.",
